snippet.textDisplay: COVID never went away nor have I treated it as if it has gone away. I continue to mask and avoid crowds, gatherings, restaurants, bars, gyms. Nothing has changed for me. I don't care if I'm the only one in the place with a mask on.. I am not going near a restaurant. In  addition to high prices and poor food, there's no reason to go to a restaurant.

snippet.textDisplay: You are not alone!! I am the same way and am completely in the minority here. Caring for my immunocompromised family members, but even if not...I don't want to risk catching anything or developing long term side effects, so I would continue to mask and social distance regardless.
